The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Ever-Ready win big
 Grey scored a brace Shillong: Calcutta outfit Ever-Ready whipped Manipur Police 5-0 in a group B match of the second division National Football League on Friday. Eugene Grey and Ernest Jeremiah scored two goals each and Surajit Chakraborty netted one. Ever-Ready had drawn 0-0 with BSF in their first match. Grey opened scoring in the 20th minute after being set up by Jayanta Sen and made it 2-0 six minutes later. Jeremiah dashed the Manipur teams comeback hopes with his first goal two minutes into the second session. He played a role in the fourth goal too as Chakraborty headed the ball in when Jeremiahs shot came off the goalkeeper in the 51st minute. Jeremiah completed the tally in the 75th minute. Ever-Ready are leading the four-team group with four points and play their last match against ITI on May 5.  (PTI)  Copyright 
